The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	Calcutta: India international Subrata Paul and Steven Dias aim to follow the footsteps of their countrymate Sunil Chetri trying their luck in Major League Soccer (MLS).     
	In fact, Chetris British-Indian agent Yogesh Joshee has apparently arranged for trials in some MLS clubs.        
	Calcutta: Soccer coach Dr Pradip Dutta has been inducted into the Asian Football Confederations prestigious elite panel of instructors.      
	Help for Becks   
	Colombo: Sri Lanka president Mahinda Rajapaksa has offered the services of his spiritual healer and personal physician, Eliyantha Lindsay White, to injured footballer David Beckham so that the England star can get back on the field within three days. White has worked with Sachin Tendulkar, Ashish Nehra and Gautam Gambhir.  
	Lifters banned  
	New Delhi: The Indian Weightlifting Federation, Saturday, handed life bans to three lifters  G. Damodaran (105 kg), Rajesh Kumar Singh (94kg) and 2006 Commonwealth Games silver medallist Vicky Bhatta (56 kg)  for a second dope offence.  
	Fiji hope  
	Wellington: Fijis national Olympic committee has encouraged its athletes to keep training for the Commonwealth Games in October as it awaits a decision from the Court of Abritration for Sport on its ban from the games.  
	Rana cleared  
	Karachi: The Pakistan Cricket Boards disciplinary committee has cleared all-rounder Rana Naved-ul Hasan of ball tampering charges during the national T20 Championship. Naved has already been banned for 12 months and fined two million rupees for violating the code of conduct in Australia.       
	Lahore: PCB made it clear Saturday that they are considering written communication from Shahid Afridi and Younis Khan as letters and not appeals against the penalties imposed on them.                                                                                                                                                      
